# Lovable Cloud Supabase

This is a **Lovable project**. Supabase is provisioned and managed by **Lovable Cloud**, not a standalone Supabase account the team logs into.

## Never ask the user to

- Run `supabase` CLI commands (`db push`, `migration up`, `functions deploy`, `seed`, etc.)
- Log into the Supabase dashboard to run SQL, seeds, or RLS changes
- Manually apply migrations or invoke edge functions from Supabase UI
- Obtain or configure service-role keys for local use

## How backend changes get applied

1. **Sync code to Lovable** — push to GitHub (Lovable pulls) or edit/prompt in the [Lovable project](https://lovable.dev/projects/7e586b0b-76b3-4989-b48d-ba4a31a775f9)
2. **Ask Lovable to apply schema/functions** — e.g. "Apply migrations in `supabase/migrations/` and deploy edge functions"
3. **Use in-app actions when available** — e.g. Admin **Load Demo Data** (`seedAllDemoData` via anon client), not CLI seed

## Local development

- `npm run dev` → `http://localhost:8080`
- Localhost uses **remote Lovable Cloud Supabase** via `.env` (`VITE_SUPABASE_URL`, `VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY`)
- No local Supabase instance; `.env` must match the Lovable project (copy from Lovable project settings if missing)
- Edge functions and migrations only exist remotely **after** Lovable sync — client code falls back to local mock AI when `analyze-document` is not deployed

## When planning work

- Prefer client-side fallbacks for demos until Lovable has deployed schema/functions
- Document "sync to Lovable first" steps instead of Supabase CLI runbooks
